{"key":"post-19454299","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19454299</id>\n<content>You don't need a hygrometer.&amp;nbsp; The humidity in the air is irrelevant.&amp;nbsp; The humidity at the pinning surface of your cakes is what matters and this is why we mist a few times daily.&amp;nbsp; Misting replaces the moisture which naturally evaporates from the substrates as a result of the fresh air exchange.&amp;nbsp; This ebb and flow of moisture content is a major pinning trigger.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The overspray from misting keeps the perlite damp, so it should never dry out during the growing cycle.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19454339</next>\n<prev>19454258</prev>\n<first>19454088</first>\n<last>19455299</last>\n<when>1390354762</when>\n<utime>01/22/14 03:39 AM</utime>\n</post>"}